  1633‚Üí### Testing
  1635‚Üí`Result` instances have two unsafe methods, aptly called `_unsafeUnwrap` and `_unsafeUnwrapErr` which **should only be used in a test environment**.
  1636‚Üí
  1637‚Üí`_unsafeUnwrap` takes a `Result<T, E>` and returns a `T` when the result is an `Ok`, otherwise it throws a custom object.
  1638‚Üí
